President Uhuru Kenyatta has signed several Bills into law, including the Finance Bill which gives low-income earners tax relief.Uhuru also signed the Civil Aviation (Amendment) Bill 2016, the Water Bill, as well as the Natural Resources Bill. The Finance Act removes excise duty on locally assembled motor vehicles and motor cycles to promote assembly.It also gives tax amnesty for taxpayers who have investments outside Kenya to reinvest back home and grants VAT exemption for park entry fees and tour operators to promote tourism.The new act also grants VAT exemption for inputs for the manufacture of animal feeds to reduce the cost of production.